WEBVTT

00:04.437 --> 00:05.405 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.438 --> 00:07.240 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.273 --> 00:12.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: It's
Tax Day, and
that's sparking new calls for
President Donald

00:12.278 --> 00:15.081 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Trump to release his own tax
returns.

00:15.115 --> 00:18.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We dig into how transparent this
White House
is.

00:18.885 --> 00:25.291 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: British Prime Minister
Theresa May calls
for a snap election, as she
seeks more public

00:25.325 --> 00:29.396 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
support to take Britain out of
the European
Union.

00:29.429 --> 00:34.634 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And a teacher in the Navajo
Nation schools
takes a very hands-on approach
to learning.

00:34.667 --> 00:37.670 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE, Teacher, Kayenta
Unified School
District: In a math class, you
get the problem

00:37.704 --> 00:40.874 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wrong, you miss that question.

00:40.907 --> 00:45.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In my program, if you get that
math problem
wrong, that animal can die.

00:45.745 --> 00:53.286 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:53.319 --> 00:56.156 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:56.189 --> 01:06.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Voting is in the
news across
Europe today, starting with a
surprise announcement

01:06.166 --> 01:07.867 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from London.

01:07.901 --> 01:12.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
British Prime Minister Theresa
May called
for an early election, in June,
instead of

01:12.505 --> 01:14.541 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
waiting until 2020.

01:14.574 --> 01:19.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Speaking outside her official
residence, May
said she is asking to move up
the vote to

01:19.446 --> 01:23.850 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
strengthen her hand in
negotiating Britain's
exit from the European Union.

01:23.883 --> 01:28.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
THERESA MAY, British Prime
Minister: Division
in Westminster will risk our
ability to make

01:28.188 --> 01:35.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a success of Brexit, and it will
cause damaging
uncertainty and instability to
the country.

01:35.495 --> 01:41.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we need a general election,
and we need
one now, because we have at this
moment a

01:41.835 --> 01:43.603 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
one-off chance to get this done.

01:43.636 --> 01:48.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will take a
closer look
at the implications of May's
move later in

01:48.274 --> 01:50.210 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the program.

01:50.243 --> 01:55.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Police in France say they have
broken up an
imminent attack aimed at that
country's presidential

01:55.215 --> 01:56.883 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
election.

01:56.916 --> 02:01.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They arrested two suspects today
in the port
city of Marseille, and recovered
guns and

02:01.187 --> 02:02.422 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
explosives.

02:02.455 --> 02:05.458 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Prosecutors accuse the pair of
being Islamic
extremists.

02:05.492 --> 02:10.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The first round of voting in
France's presidential
race begins on Sunday.

02:10.330 --> 02:16.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Turkey, the main opposition
party is formally
asking to annul Sunday's
referendum that expanded

02:16.803 --> 02:19.606 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the powers of President Recep
Tayyip Erdogan.

02:19.639 --> 02:25.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hundreds of people waited
outside the electoral
board's headquarters today to
file petitions

02:25.111 --> 02:26.479 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
against the vote.

02:26.513 --> 02:30.783 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say accepting ballots
without an official
stamp was illegal.

02:30.817 --> 02:36.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Separately, the White House
defended President
Trump's congratulatory call to
Erdogan, arguing

02:36.789 --> 02:40.593 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that he is an ally in the fight
against terrorism.

02:40.627 --> 02:45.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vice President Mike Pence moved
on from South
Korea to Japan today, and again
pressed the

02:45.832 --> 02:48.134 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
U.S. case against North Korea.

02:48.168 --> 02:53.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Tokyo, Mr. Pence said the
U.S. will not
relent until the Korean
Peninsula is free

02:53.606 --> 02:55.308 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of nuclear weapons.

02:55.341 --> 02:59.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he told Japanese Prime
Minister Shinzo
Abe that American support is
unwavering.

02:59.646 --> 03:05.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE PENCE, Vice President of
the United States:
We appreciate the challenging
times in which

03:05.118 --> 03:11.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the people of Japan live, with
increasing
provocations from across the Sea
of Japan.

03:11.224 --> 03:20.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as the president himself
would if he
was here, let me be clear to
you, Mr. Prime

03:20.333 --> 03:22.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Minister and to all of people in
Japan, we
are with you 100 percent.

03:22.969 --> 03:26.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Last week, the
White House
announced that a U.S. aircraft
carrier was

03:26.673 --> 03:30.210 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
steaming toward Korean waters as
a deterrent.

03:30.243 --> 03:32.912 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now it turns out that was
premature.

03:32.946 --> 03:38.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reports that
the carrier
group was headed the opposite
way at the time,

03:38.151 --> 03:39.619 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before changing course.

03:39.652 --> 03:43.423 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Pentagon blames a series of
miscommunications.

03:43.456 --> 03:48.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. military says it
intercepted two
Russian bombers in international
airspace

03:48.194 --> 03:50.230 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
off Alaska on Monday.

03:50.263 --> 03:54.234 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two U.S. fighter planes shadowed
them for
12 minutes.

03:54.267 --> 04:00.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
According to FOX News, the
Russians came within
100 miles of Alaska's Kodiak
Island.

04:00.240 --> 04:03.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is the first such incident in
nearly two
years.

04:03.943 --> 04:09.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The manhunt is over for the
suspect accused
of killing an elderly man in
Cleveland and

04:09.649 --> 04:12.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
posting video of the crime on
Facebook.

04:12.552 --> 04:16.889 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State police in Pennsylvania
found Steve Stephens
today in the city of Erie.

04:16.923 --> 04:22.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He shot and killed himself after
a chase,
closing the case for authorities
back in Cleveland.

04:22.528 --> 04:26.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CALVIN WILLIAMS, Cleveland,
Ohio, Police Chief:
We are grateful that this has
ended.

04:26.165 --> 04:31.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We would have preferred that it
had not ended
this way, because there are a
lot of questions,

04:31.104 --> 04:36.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm sure, not only for the
family, but the
city in general, would have had
for Steve

04:36.876 --> 04:38.611 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as to why this transpired.

04:38.645 --> 04:43.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Facebook CEO Mark
Zuckerberg
pledged today that the social
media giant

04:44.017 --> 04:49.589 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will do all it can to prevent
postings of
violent crimes in the future.

04:49.622 --> 04:54.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
State officials in Arkansas are
vowing to
carry out a double execution
later this week,

04:54.260 --> 04:58.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that after the U.S. Supreme
Court halted the
state's plan to resume capital
punishment

04:58.831 --> 05:01.601 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for the first time in nearly 12
years.

05:01.634 --> 05:06.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The high court issued its ruling
late Monday,
just minutes before a condemned
man was scheduled

05:06.706 --> 05:08.574 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to die.

05:08.608 --> 05:14.280 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary of Homeland Security
John Kelly
is taking on critics in Congress
over immigration

05:14.314 --> 05:16.149 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
enforcement.

05:16.182 --> 05:20.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Washington today, Kelly said
that too many
public officials ridicule
immigration agents

05:21.020 --> 05:26.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and airport security officers,
and accept
unfounded allegations about them
as truth.

05:26.793 --> 05:30.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KELLY, U.S. Homeland
Security Secretary:
If lawmakers do not like the
laws that we

05:30.363 --> 05:35.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
enforce, that we are charged to
enforce, that
we are sworn to enforce, then
they should

05:35.501 --> 05:40.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have the courage and the skill
to change the
laws.

05:40.506 --> 05:43.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Otherwise, they should shut up
and support
the men and women on the front
lines.

05:43.543 --> 05:48.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: More than 21,000
undocumented
immigrants in the U.S. have been
arrested

05:48.881 --> 05:51.150 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
since President Trump took
office.

05:51.184 --> 05:55.421 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is up from 16,000 at this
point a year
ago.

05:55.455 --> 06:00.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republicans faced another tough
race today
in what had been a solidly red
U.S. congressional

06:00.727 --> 06:02.462 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
district.

06:02.495 --> 06:06.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The election was in suburban
Atlanta, where
18 candidates from both parties
competed.

06:06.899 --> 06:12.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The seat was vacated by Tom
Price, who is
now the secretary of health and
human services.

06:12.071 --> 06:17.243 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
President Trump sharply
criticized the leading
Democrat in the race, Jon
Ossoff, who said

06:17.276 --> 06:20.813 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he thinks the president is --
quote -- "misinformed."

06:20.847 --> 06:25.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is word this evening that
President
George H.W. Bush is hospitalized
again in

06:25.518 --> 06:27.153 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Houston.

06:27.186 --> 06:30.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A spokesman said Mr. Bush is
doing fine and
already on the path to going
home.

06:30.957 --> 06:32.392 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He gave no other details.

06:32.425 --> 06:33.826 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Mr. Bush is 92.

06:33.860 --> 06:38.331 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He was hospitalized for
pneumonia back in
January.

06:38.364 --> 06:43.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on Wall Street, stocks lost
more ground
after Goldman Sachs and Johnson
&amp; Johnson

06:43.403 --> 06:44.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
posted disappointing earnings.

06:44.771 --> 06:49.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost 113
points to close at 20523.

06:49.709 --> 06:56.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell seven, and the
S&amp;P 500 slid
nearly seven.

06:56.282 --> 07:01.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
growing concerns
over White House ethics; the
president's efforts

07:01.721 --> 07:08.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to revamp a widely used guest
workers program;
pushback against Mr. Trump's
upcoming state

07:09.028 --> 07:22.975 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
visit to Britain; and much more.

07:23.009 --> 07:28.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's Tax Day, I'm sure you know,
and President
Trump is facing renewed
questions over public

07:28.748 --> 07:32.618 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
disclosure issues that dogged
him on the campaign
trial.

07:32.652 --> 07:34.520 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Our John Yang begins our
coverage.

07:34.554 --> 07:41.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: For President Trump,
questions
about transparency start with
his taxes, and

07:41.060 --> 07:45.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
why he's breaking with tradition
and not releasing
his returns.

07:45.164 --> 07:46.899 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
White House Press Secretary Sean
Spicer:

07:46.933 --> 07:49.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
We're under the same audit that
has existed,

07:49.635 --> 07:51.504 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and so nothing has changed.

07:51.537 --> 07:56.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: In fact, presidents
and vice presidents
are automatically audited by the
IRS, which

07:56.976 --> 07:59.879 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hasn't stopped other chief
executives from
making them public.

07:59.912 --> 08:04.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This weekend, thousands of
people marched
in cities around the country to
demand that

08:04.250 --> 08:06.552 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump release his taxes.

08:06.586 --> 08:12.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He dismissed them with a tweet:
"Someone should
look into who paid for the small
organized

08:12.191 --> 08:13.159 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
rallies.

08:13.192 --> 08:14.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The election is over."

08:14.994 --> 08:20.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump is the first president
in more than
40 years not to make his tax
returns public.

08:20.600 --> 08:23.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The president says only
reporters care about
the issue.

08:23.603 --> 08:29.375 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
But in a recent
Bloomberg/Morning Consult
poll, 53 percent of those
surveyed said the

08:29.408 --> 08:31.844 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
president should release them.

08:31.878 --> 08:36.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then there's the question of who
visits the
White House, which Mr. Trump
calls the people's

08:36.682 --> 08:38.484 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
house.

08:38.518 --> 08:42.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The administration says it's
ending the Obama
policy of making visitor logs
available, with

08:42.622 --> 08:46.359 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
exceptions for national security
and privacy
reasons.

08:46.392 --> 08:48.160 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Press Secretary Spicer:

08:48.194 --> 08:52.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER: Frankly, the faux
attempt that
the Obama administration put
out, where they

08:52.064 --> 08:56.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would scrub who they didn't want
put out,
didn't serve anyone well.

08:56.168 --> 09:00.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: The administration is
also under
scrutiny for hiring former
lobbyists to craft

09:00.907 --> 09:03.809 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
policies for the industries they
came from.

09:03.843 --> 09:08.748 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The New York Times and
ProPublica found some
had been given secret waivers
exempting them

09:08.781 --> 09:10.683 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from ethics rules.

09:10.716 --> 09:15.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ethics questions also extend to
first daughter
and White House adviser Ivanka
Trump and her

09:15.087 --> 09:16.989 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
business interests.

09:17.023 --> 09:22.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Associated Press reported
that she received
provisional Chinese approval for
three trademarks

09:22.161 --> 09:27.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the day she dined with
president Xi Jinping
at Mr. Trump's Mar-a-Lago
resort.

09:27.600 --> 09:32.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Her fashion line, which is
seeing record sales,
is held in a family-run trust,
and she has

09:32.972 --> 09:36.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pledged to recuse herself from
issues that
present conflicts.

09:36.842 --> 09:38.945 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang.

09:38.978 --> 09:43.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For more on some
of the questions
all of this raises about
government transparency

09:43.549 --> 09:46.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and conflicts of interest, we
are joined by
Richard Painter.

09:46.752 --> 09:51.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's a University of Minnesota
law professor
who served as President George
W. Bush's top

09:51.991 --> 09:53.693 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ethics attorney.

09:53.726 --> 09:58.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Noah Bookbinder, he's
executive director
of the government watchdog group
Citizens

09:58.364 --> 10:01.434 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for Responsibility and Ethics in
Washington.

10:01.467 --> 10:03.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We welcome both of you to the
program.

10:03.302 --> 10:04.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NOAH BOOKBINDER, Executive
Director, Citizens
for Responsibility and Ethics in
Washington:

10:04.170 --> 10:05.137 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

10:05.171 --> 10:06.138 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thank you.

10:06.172 --> 10:07.139 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Noah Bookbinder, I'm going to
start with you.

10:07.173 --> 10:08.140 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's so much to cover here.

10:08.174 --> 10:09.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Let's just pick out a few of
these questions.

10:09.475 --> 10:11.377 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Taxes.

10:11.410 --> 10:16.816 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The White House continues to
insist that President
Trump's taxes are being audited,
and there's

10:16.849 --> 10:21.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just no way he can release them,
he doesn't
have that ability to release
them.

10:21.120 --> 10:22.088 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What's the answer?

10:22.121 --> 10:24.790 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NOAH BOOKBINDER: That's just not
correct.

10:24.824 --> 10:30.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As the report just indicated,
every president's
taxes are routinely audited, and
yet all of

10:30.363 --> 10:34.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the previous presidents have
seen fit to release
