29:34.472 --> 29:36.040 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It will be incredibly quick.

29:36.074 --> 29:37.842 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is not unexpected.

29:37.876 --> 29:41.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There were many people amongst
all of the
different parties who thought
that she would

29:41.279 --> 29:42.514 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
call it.

29:42.547 --> 29:44.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The timing, of course, caught
many people
by surprise.

29:44.949 --> 29:50.855 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Stephanie Baker
of Bloomberg
in London, thank you very much.

29:50.889 --> 30:04.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now, from the
prime minister's
surprise news of today, to a
surprise Theresa

30:04.302 --> 30:10.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
May brought to the White House
in January,
and the debate it's sparked
across Great Britain.

30:10.542 --> 30:14.712 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From London, special
correspondent Ryan Chilcote
has this look.

30:14.746 --> 30:21.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: It was supposed
to be a diplomatic
coup, the British prime minister
beating the

30:21.586 --> 30:23.354 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
world's leaders to the Oval
Office.

30:23.388 --> 30:29.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
I am honored to have Prime
Minister Theresa

30:29.761 --> 30:32.697 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
May here for our first official
visit.

30:32.730 --> 30:35.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: May didn't just
return the
favor.

30:35.600 --> 30:40.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She upped the ante, extending an
honor only
two U.S. presidents have
received since 1952.

30:40.738 --> 30:44.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
THERESA MAY, British Prime
Minister: I have
today been able to convey Her
Majesty the

30:44.609 --> 30:49.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Queen's hope that President
Trump and the
first lady would pay a state
visit to the

30:49.080 --> 30:53.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
United Kingdom later this year,
and I'm delighted
the president has accepted that
invitation.

30:53.918 --> 30:57.722 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Then, things got
awkward.

30:57.755 --> 31:06.264 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Three days later, 20,000
protesters gathered
outside the prime minister's
office to denounce

31:06.297 --> 31:13.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the travel ban President Trump
imposed just
hours after May left, then,
another day of

31:13.037 --> 31:21.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
demonstrations, then another --
1.8 million
Brits signed a petition
demanding the prime

31:21.412 --> 31:23.348 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
minister cancel the state visit.

31:23.381 --> 31:28.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If 10 of the last 12 American
presidents who'd
come weren't given the honor,
why should President

31:28.653 --> 31:30.054 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Trump?

31:30.088 --> 31:31.789 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Parliament gathered for a
debate.

31:31.823 --> 31:34.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAULA SHERRIFF, Parliament
Member: Does he
agree that to use the expression
grab them

31:34.626 --> 31:39.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by the (EXPLETIVE DELETED)
describes a sexual
assault, and therefore suggests
that he shouldn't

31:39.464 --> 31:41.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be afforded a visit to our
queen?

31:41.900 --> 31:47.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: At 82, Paul Flynn
is the senior
member of the House of Commons.

31:47.138 --> 31:50.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The debate in this country isn't
about whether
Donald Trump comes here.

31:50.308 --> 31:53.745 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's been about whether he is
treated to a
state visit.

31:53.778 --> 31:55.513 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What's the big deal?

31:55.546 --> 31:57.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL FLYNN, Parliament Member:
The big deal
is that only two American
presidents since

31:57.982 --> 32:02.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
1952 have been given this
special honor of
a state visit.

32:02.186 --> 32:07.058 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we're giving this unique
privilege to
Donald Trump after being in
office for seven

32:07.091 --> 32:08.493 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
days.

32:08.526 --> 32:12.297 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was an act of desperation by
a prime minister
that's in deep trouble.

32:12.330 --> 32:17.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're losing our markets in
Europe because
of Brexit, and she's desperate
to ingratiate

32:17.669 --> 32:21.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
herself with America in order to
try to win
new markets.

32:21.873 --> 32:23.675 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't want to give him
privileged treatment.

32:23.708 --> 32:26.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We want to show him our contempt
and disdain.

32:26.611 --> 32:32.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: President Trump's
visit to
the U.K. has become politically
fraught.

32:32.150 --> 32:36.487 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Every aspect of the trip, from
the timing
to the itinerary, is in flux.

32:36.521 --> 32:37.822 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: Barack Obama.

32:37.855 --> 32:39.791 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

32:39.824 --> 32:44.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Six years ago,
President Trump's
predecessor was granted the
highest of honors

32:44.562 --> 32:49.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the opportunity to address
Parliament during
his state visit.

32:49.400 --> 32:53.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was ruled out this time
around before
it could even be debated.

32:53.304 --> 32:55.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
John Bercow is the speaker of
the House of
Commons.

32:55.773 --> 33:01.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BERCOW, Speaker, House of
Commons: Before
the imposition of the migrant
ban, I would

33:01.913 --> 33:09.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
myself have been strongly
opposed to an address
by President Trump in
Westminster Hall.

33:09.320 --> 33:18.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After the imposition of the
migrant ban by
President Trump, I am even more
strongly opposed.

33:18.196 --> 33:24.769 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: The state banquet
is a staple
of state visits, so that's in.

33:24.802 --> 33:29.240 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Protests are also a regular
feature.

33:29.273 --> 33:35.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A foray into the countryside
kept London's
protesters away from President
Bush in 2003

33:35.346 --> 33:37.081 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
during his state visit.

33:37.115 --> 33:42.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This time, the planners are
looking at going
even further, to the north.

33:42.186 --> 33:43.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Scotland's an option.

33:43.988 --> 33:48.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rural and remote, it's not a
likely place
for tens of thousands of
protesters to gather,

33:49.027 --> 33:55.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and yet, even here, not
everyone's a fan.

33:55.433 --> 34:00.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump owns two golf
courses in Scotland,
including this one built on a
pristine patch

34:00.471 --> 34:05.243 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of 4,000-year-old sand dunes.

34:05.276 --> 34:10.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
David Milne's house overlooks
the course and
the sea, or at least it did,
until he refused

34:10.748 --> 34:13.117 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to sell his property to
President Trump.

34:13.151 --> 34:16.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you used have a completely
unimpeded view
here.

34:16.854 --> 34:19.624 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID MILNE, Scotland: Yes, we
had 40 miles
of uninterrupted coastline.

34:19.657 --> 34:22.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: And now you have
got the fence.

34:22.693 --> 34:25.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID MILNE: Yes, and Trump
provided the trees,
which, as you can see, are dying
slowly.

34:25.797 --> 34:30.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Milne has flown
two flags ever
since Trump visited Scotland
last year.

34:30.968 --> 34:33.504 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The one on top is Scotland's.

34:33.538 --> 34:35.573 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And what possessed you to put up
a Mexican
flag?

34:35.606 --> 34:39.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID MILNE: Donald Trump had
recently made
the announcement that he was
going to build

34:39.210 --> 34:41.813 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a border wall and send the bill
to Mexico.

34:41.846 --> 34:45.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, he did basically the same
thing here
with a small fence, and he sent
me the bill.

34:45.616 --> 34:47.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Michael Forbes
wouldn't sell
either.

34:47.318 --> 34:52.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL FORBES, Scotland: The
first thing
he said is was, what's this land
worth?

34:52.256 --> 34:54.459 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Twenty-five dollars an acre.

34:54.492 --> 34:57.762 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
(EXPLETIVE DELETED) I said in
your (EXPLETIVE
DELETED) dreams.

34:57.795 --> 34:58.996 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

34:59.030 --> 35:01.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHAEL FORBES: Yes, there will
be protesters,
all right.

35:01.432 --> 35:06.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: If there's one
place in all
of the United Kingdom that can
provide security

35:06.571 --> 35:15.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and privacy during President
Trump's visit,
it's here at the queen's holiday
home in Scotland.

35:15.379 --> 35:19.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump has reportedly
asked to play
golf on the queen's private
course at her

35:19.117 --> 35:23.121 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Scottish castle, Balmoral.

35:23.154 --> 35:24.822 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That would be a real honor.

35:24.856 --> 35:29.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The last president Queen
Elizabeth II met
at her private home was Dwight
Eisenhower

35:29.994 --> 35:31.429 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in 1959.

35:31.462 --> 35:36.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NARRATOR: He went to Balmoral to
stay with
the royal family, remember?

35:36.567 --> 35:41.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: According to one
poll, close
to half of the British public
supports the

35:41.539 --> 35:43.441 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
idea of a state visit.

35:43.474 --> 35:48.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is also support for the
president, himself,
though in all of the
parliamentary debate,

35:48.279 --> 35:50.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this was the closest anyone got
to it.

35:50.081 --> 35:52.717 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NIGEL EVANS, Member of
Parliament: I would
like to respect the fact that he
stood on

35:52.750 --> 35:55.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a platform which is he is now
delivering.

35:55.520 --> 36:00.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's going to go down in history
as being
roundly condemned for being the
only politician

36:00.625 --> 36:02.393 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to deliver on his promises.

36:02.426 --> 36:07.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Most who back the
visit, though,
do so despite the president's
policies.

36:07.265 --> 36:13.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's a selfie that Hillary
took up in Derry,
New Hampshire, in January last
year.

36:13.070 --> 36:17.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Sir Simon Burns
traveled to
the U.S. to campaign on behalf
of Hillary

36:17.808 --> 36:19.277 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Clinton.

36:19.310 --> 36:22.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is a conservative member of
Parliament
who supports the state visit.

36:22.380 --> 36:24.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SIR SIMON BURNS, Member of
Parliament: We
stand by America.

36:24.348 --> 36:25.416 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
America stands by us.

36:25.449 --> 36:27.118 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's in our national interest.

36:27.151 --> 36:31.789 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And regardless of who's
president, we have
got to get on with the United
States.

36:31.822 --> 36:36.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: Fellow member of
Parliament
Bob Neill says the visit should
be looked

36:36.060 --> 36:37.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at in perspective.

36:37.895 --> 36:40.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BOB NEILL, Member of Parliament:
We have had
out-and-out dictators like
Nicolae Ceausescu

36:40.998 --> 36:43.601 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and Robert Mugabe come over in
the past.

36:43.634 --> 36:48.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, whatever my personal
distaste for Mr.
Trump's style and policies in
some areas,

36:49.006 --> 36:50.875 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he's a democratically elected
politician.

36:50.908 --> 36:56.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RYAN CHILCOTE: President Trump
and Prime Minister
May have agreed to postpone the
visit until

36:56.447 --> 37:00.384 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
October to give British
protesters a chance
to cool off.

37:00.418 --> 37:10.361 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Reporting for the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm Ryan
Chilcote in London.

37:10.394 --> 37:21.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Fallout from
Sunday's referendum
vote in Turkey continued today,
with critics

37:21.439 --> 37:26.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
