with its ranking
member, Democratic Senator Ben
Cardin of Maryland.

37:38.356 --> 37:44.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I began by asking him if he was
concerned
by President Trump's call last
night to President

37:44.061 --> 37:46.731 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Erdogan to congratulate him on
his apparent
victory.

37:46.764 --> 37:48.532 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

37:48.566 --> 37:52.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BEN CARDIN (D), Maryland: Well,
Turkey is
a very vibrant democracy, and
it's, of course,

37:52.103 --> 37:53.871 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
one of our NATO allies.

37:53.904 --> 37:55.106 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They had a referendum.

37:55.139 --> 37:58.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The referendum, according to
local officials,
did pass.

37:58.643 --> 38:03.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are certainly concerned about
some of the
powers that are being
consolidated by Mr.

38:03.147 --> 38:07.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Erdogan, and about the checks
and balances
in their own system.

38:07.385 --> 38:12.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's also been questions
raised as to the
legitimacy of some of the votes
that were

38:12.757 --> 38:14.191 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cast.

38:14.225 --> 38:16.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there are still issues that
I think need
to be addressed by Turkey.

38:16.294 --> 38:21.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As far as President Trump
calling President
Erdogan, that's a personal
decision he made.

38:22.033 --> 38:25.002 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it's important to
recognize this is
an important ally.

38:25.036 --> 38:30.041 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And so you are
watching the
way ballots were cast?

38:30.074 --> 38:35.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I ask because European observers
are saying
that some 2.5 million ballots
may have been

38:35.579 --> 38:36.547 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
cast fraudulently.

38:36.580 --> 38:37.648 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

38:37.682 --> 38:39.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: Yes, I'm very
concerned about
that.

38:39.850 --> 38:43.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's been some legitimate
concerns raised
about some of the techniques
that were used

38:43.721 --> 38:47.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the way the election was
conducted.

38:47.458 --> 38:48.426 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So we are concerned.

38:48.459 --> 38:49.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It was a close election.

38:49.694 --> 38:52.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was not a -- it was a pretty
close call
between the two.

38:52.363 --> 38:57.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The amount of resources that
were made available
were certainly not equal on both
sides.

38:57.902 --> 39:02.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are some questions on some
of the processes
that -- procedures that were
used.

39:02.540 --> 39:04.342 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, yes, we are concerned.

39:04.375 --> 39:08.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we hope that the Erdogan
government will
have a complete independent
investigation

39:08.646 --> 39:10.614 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on how the elections itself were
conducted.

39:10.648 --> 39:12.383 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let me turn you
to North Korea.

39:12.416 --> 39:17.555 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
