raised significantly
just in the last few days.

39:17.588 --> 39:21.659 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rhetoric, both from the
United States,
from the Trump administration,
and from the

39:21.692 --> 39:24.995 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
North Koreans, has gotten
hotter.

39:25.029 --> 39:31.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This administration is saying
what they call
the era of strategic patience is
over.

39:31.202 --> 39:34.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last night on this program, I
interviewed
the former Defense Secretary
William Perry,

39:34.805 --> 39:39.577 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who said he's alarmed by the
state of relations
between our two countries.

39:39.610 --> 39:40.578 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Where do you stand?

39:40.611 --> 39:41.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How concerned are you?

39:41.812 --> 39:42.780 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

39:42.813 --> 39:44.348 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: Well, I'm very, very
concerned.

39:44.382 --> 39:48.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Clearly, the young leader of
North Korea is
a very dangerous person.

39:48.352 --> 39:50.221 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're not sure how he makes
decisions.

39:50.254 --> 39:55.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have seen what he does to
people who oppose
him, including members of his
own family.

39:55.659 --> 39:57.628 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's not a stable leader.

39:57.661 --> 40:02.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now is the time for the United
States to exercise
some very mature international
leadership

40:03.000 --> 40:08.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to try to calm things down on
the Korean Peninsula,
and to change the calculation
for North Korea,

40:08.773 --> 40:15.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so that it's -- they recognize
it's in their
interests to negotiate the end
of the nuclear

40:15.146 --> 40:16.981 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
weapon program.

40:17.014 --> 40:23.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
