with the international
community.

40:31.829 --> 40:35.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That requires strong, mature
U.S. leadership.

40:35.299 --> 40:39.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We need a game plan that can
accomplish those
types of objectives on the
Korean Peninsula.

40:39.370 --> 40:42.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are you seeing
that game plan
from this administration?

40:42.873 --> 40:44.408 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

40:44.442 --> 40:47.478 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: No, I'm not -- I'm
not clear what
the administration's policy is.

40:47.511 --> 40:49.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They haven't really shared that
with Congress.

40:49.146 --> 40:53.350 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I'm not sure they have a
comprehensive policy
for the Korean Peninsula.

40:53.384 --> 40:58.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We want to make sure that North
Korea doesn't
possess the ability to use
nuclear weapons,

40:58.856 --> 41:02.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
particularly to be able to
deliver those nuclear
weapons through the missiles
that they are

41:02.526 --> 41:06.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
testing, and that we want to
make sure also
that North Korea is more in
harmony with the

41:06.597 --> 41:09.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
international community in the
way they treat
its own people.

41:09.967 --> 41:13.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, and, obviously, we're
concerned about
the security of South Korea.

41:13.771 --> 41:17.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there's a lot of interest
that the United
States has on the Korean
Peninsula.

41:17.241 --> 41:21.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And we haven't seen an
articulated, coordinated
policy from this administration.

41:21.846 --> 41:23.614 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We're moving
around the world.

41:23.647 --> 41:28.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's so much to ask you
about, Senator,
but I also want to speak to you
about Russia.

41:28.552 --> 41:33.424 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Besides Russian meddling in U.S.
elections,
there's now growing concern
about Russian

41:33.457 --> 41:37.094 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
involvement in upcoming
elections in France
and in Germany.

41:37.127 --> 41:45.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You are the sponsor, along with
others, a
bipartisan bill in the Senate to
impose sanctions

41:45.102 --> 41:49.340 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on Russia for cyber-activity.

41:49.373 --> 41:51.775 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was -- that legislation was
introduced
months ago.

41:51.809 --> 41:53.978 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Russians are still doing
this.

41:54.011 --> 42:01.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Do they -- what's your sense of
how seriously
they take any sort of
retaliation or action

42:01.151 --> 42:02.119 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by the U.S.?

42:02.152 --> 42:04.054 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

42:04.088 --> 42:07.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: Well, we do know
that the sanctions
that were led by the United
States, and which

42:07.658 --> 42:12.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Europe has joined us, has had a
major impact
on the Russian economy.

42:12.162 --> 42:17.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we believe sanctions can be
very effective
in changing the equation for
Russia and what

42:17.501 --> 42:22.540 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they're doing, not just in
meddling in our
elections or meddling in
European elections,

42:22.573 --> 42:27.978 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but what they're doing in
Ukraine and the
annexation of Crimea -- there's
still engagement

42:28.012 --> 42:32.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on the eastern part of Ukraine
-- and the
manner in which they are
supporting the Assad

42:32.116 --> 42:34.919 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
regime in Syria committing war
crimes.

42:34.952 --> 42:40.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All those behaviors by Russia,
we believe,
need to change, and we believe
sanctions can

42:40.357 --> 42:42.026 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
be a major part of that.

42:42.059 --> 42:46.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, yes, we want to enhance
those sanctions
to make them stronger.

42:46.096 --> 42:52.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a strong bipartisan
group, 10 Democrats,
10 Republicans, that have joined
in this legislation.

42:52.503 --> 42:54.972 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We do know that Russia meddled
in our election.

42:55.005 --> 42:56.140 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We know that.

42:56.173 --> 42:58.309 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know that they meddled in the
Montenegro
election.

42:58.342 --> 43:00.110 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We know that and caused
violence.

43:00.144 --> 43:06.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that they're very active
today in
France and in Germany trying to
impact that

43:06.317 --> 43:11.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
election, not only impact the
integrity of
the election, but also the
results, to get

43:11.322 --> 43:15.559 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a more pro-Russian leader --
leaders in Europe.

43:15.593 --> 43:20.130 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is totally unacceptable,
and we need
to be united with our European
allies to prevent

43:20.164 --> 43:21.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that from happening.

43:21.699 --> 43:23.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And is the Trump
administration
supporting that legislation?

43:23.567 --> 43:25.336 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

43:25.369 --> 43:29.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: Well, I really have
not had much
communication with the Trump
administration

43:29.440 --> 43:31.775 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in regards to Russian policy.

43:31.809 --> 43:37.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are major players yet to
be named that
-- from the administration that
will require

43:37.181 --> 43:38.382 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Senate confirmation.

43:38.415 --> 43:42.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we're still awaiting their
full team to
be in place.

43:42.386 --> 43:45.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In my conversations with Mr.
Tillerson, I
have made it very clear.

43:45.589 --> 43:48.892 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think he's made it clear in
recent weeks.

43:48.926 --> 43:54.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we're trying to give the
administration
more tools it can use for an
effective policy

43:54.398 --> 43:56.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
against Russia's aggressive
actions.

43:56.500 --> 44:01.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator Ben
Cardin, the ranking
Democrat on the Senate Foreign
Relations Committee,

44:01.505 --> 44:02.473 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
thank you very much.

44:02.506 --> 44:03.540 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

44:03.574 --> 44:08.545 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BEN CARDIN: Thank you, Judy.

44:08.579 --> 44:21.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: a classroom
innovation
called career and technical
education, a hands-on

44:21.058 --> 44:23.360 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
learning method for high school
students.

44:23.394 --> 44:27.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is seen as a practical
approach for both
those headed to college and for
those who

44:27.765 --> 44:29.099 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
are not.

44:29.133 --> 44:32.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in the Navajo Nation in
Arizona, it's
making a difference.

44:32.836 --> 44:38.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PBS special correspondent Lisa
Stark of our
partner Education Week brings us
this story

44:38.409 --> 44:41.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as part of our weekly segment
Making the Grade.

44:41.745 --> 44:46.116 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA STARK: This is a
one-of-a-kind classroom,
with a one-of-a-kind educator,
Clyde McBride.

44:46.150 --> 44:49.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE, Teacher, Kayenta
Unified School
District: My philosophy is a kid
don't learn

44:49.687 --> 44:51.355 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
unless they get a little dirty.

44:51.388 --> 44:57.795 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA STARK: So, in Clyde
McBride's classes
in Navajo Nation in Northeastern
Arizona,

44:57.828 --> 44:58.796 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
students jump right in.

44:58.829 --> 45:00.631 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: You never hold
with your hands.

45:00.664 --> 45:02.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You hold with your forearm.

45:02.599 --> 45:04.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STUDENT: The McBrides tell us,
you know, go
in there.

45:04.968 --> 45:08.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You're not going to learn
anything if you
just kind of stand back and just
watch anything.

45:08.272 --> 45:14.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: This is hands-on
instruction in
veterinary science, part
classroom, part veterinary

45:14.111 --> 45:15.879 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
clinic.

45:15.913 --> 45:21.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Students work and observe in two
operating
rooms, one for small animals,
the other for

45:21.185 --> 45:23.253 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
large.

45:23.287 --> 45:31.528 align:left position:12.5%,start line:66.67% size:87.5%
They conduct exams and
vaccinations in a
state-of-the-art
$2.4 million facility, part of
Monument Valley

45:31.562 --> 45:39.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
High School in Kayenta, Arizona,
and its career
and technical education program;
180 students,

45:39.136 --> 45:43.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more than a quarter of the high
school, have
signed up for this program,
where abstract

45:43.774 --> 45:46.009 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
concepts meet the real world.

45:46.043 --> 45:51.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: Before they go to
surgery,
ketamine puts them to sleep.

45:51.949 --> 45:54.518 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is an anesthesia.

45:54.551 --> 46:00.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's calculated by the
millimeter per
pound.

46:00.824 --> 46:06.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In a math class, you get the
problem wrong,
you miss that question.

46:06.730 --> 46:11.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In my program, if you get that
math problem
wrong, that animal can die.

46:11.368 --> 46:15.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA STARK: McBride grew up
around animals
on a ranch in Arizona.

46:15.706 --> 46:21.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He lost his father at age 16 and
figured he'd
forgo college to stay home and
take care of

46:21.612 --> 46:22.746 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the cattle.

46:22.780 --> 46:24.615 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
His mother had other ideas.

46:24.648 --> 46:28.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: I will never
forget going home
one day and she says: "We're
going to sign

46:28.752 --> 46:29.720 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
papers.

46:29.753 --> 46:31.054 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I just sold the ranch.

46:31.088 --> 46:32.823 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You have got to go to college."

46:32.856 --> 46:37.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: He became a teacher
and, longing
for a rural district, jumped at
the job in

46:37.728 --> 46:39.496 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Kayenta.

46:39.530 --> 46:43.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: When I came up
here, some of
my peer teachers were like, why
go to the

46:43.600 --> 46:44.802 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
reservation?

46:44.835 --> 46:47.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's going to be the worst
place that you
ever go to.

46:47.171 --> 46:51.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our school is 98 percent on the
free and reduced
lunch program.

46:51.375 --> 46:55.078 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A lot of our communities are
very, very poor.

46:55.112 --> 47:01.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: But that hasn't
slowed McBride,
or stopped him from dreaming
big.

47:01.685 --> 47:06.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELISSA MCBRIDE, Teacher: When
Mr. McBride
and I first started dating, we
would go out

47:06.657 --> 47:14.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to eat dinner and he would draw
on napkins
his vision of the agro-science
center.

47:14.464 --> 47:18.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I would tell him all the
time, you're
crazy.

47:18.101 --> 47:22.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People don't invest money like
this in education,
especially in Native American
children.

47:22.172 --> 47:24.575 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: I wouldn't accept
no as an
answer.

47:24.608 --> 47:28.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA STARK: It took decades to
turn his dream
into a reality.

47:28.846 --> 47:35.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A new superintendent found the
funding, and
students helped with the design.

47:35.085 --> 47:38.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Ag Center opened its doors
opened in 2011.

47:38.722 --> 47:43.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This program prepares students
for careers
and college and much more.

47:43.427 --> 47:45.195 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

47:45.229 --> 47:48.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SUZANNE SMITH, Veterinarian:
It's to get the
community and the kids and the
students and

47:48.665 --> 47:54.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their parents involved in a
better lifestyle
and better health for
themselves, for their

47:54.671 --> 47:58.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
animals, and making better
career choices
and making better life choices.

47:58.976 --> 48:00.944 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: And it's working.

48:00.978 --> 48:04.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Students in the veterinary
science program
do better than the state average
on math and

48:04.781 --> 48:10.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
English tests; 100 percent of
them graduate
high school, and three-quarters
of them go

48:10.554 --> 48:12.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on to college or training
programs.

48:13.023 --> 48:19.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The rest go on to a job, numbers
that would
be impressive anywhere, but
especially for

48:19.062 --> 48:25.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Native American students, who
post the lowest
graduation rates of any racial
or ethnic group.

48:25.068 --> 48:26.870 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: We ignite the
fire.

48:26.904 --> 48:27.971 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We give them that passion.

48:28.005 --> 48:30.807 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We give them that leadership.

48:30.841 --> 48:35.412 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then whatever route they
want to choose,
then we support that route.

48:35.445 --> 48:38.482 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PRESHES PARRISH-BEGAY, Student:
They made
sure I didn't fall off track.

48:38.515 --> 48:47.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They made sure I didn't -- I
didn't do anything
to ruin my chances of going
somewhere.

48:47.090 --> 48:50.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHELIA YENCHICK, Student: I
didn't really
have that much motivation from
my parents,

48:50.827 --> 48:56.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but here, the kids, they really
have a lot
of that from the teachers and
the community.

48:56.366 --> 49:00.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They really help them a lot, and
then they
reach their goals.

49:00.237 --> 49:05.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA STARK: The program has
enriched the students
and their community.

49:05.108 --> 49:10.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
With the nearest vet hours away,
this is the
go-to clinic for the animals and
livestock

49:10.681 --> 49:13.317 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
families here depend on.

49:13.350 --> 49:16.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Animals are considered a sacred
part of the
Navajo culture.

49:16.420 --> 49:22.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MYRON HUDSON, Student: In my
culture, it's
like, if you take care of the
animals, they

49:22.592 --> 49:24.227 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
take care of you.

49:24.261 --> 49:28.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: McBride's goal is to
launch his
students on to college or good
jobs.

49:28.765 --> 49:31.335 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Many hope to come back to serve
their community.

49:31.368 --> 49:35.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CLYDE MCBRIDE: The Navajo
belief, and really
the way I was raised, is you
want to leave

49:35.939 --> 49:39.343 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this world better than you found
it.

49:39.376 --> 49:42.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I can tell you that that's
what I took
into this program.

49:42.746 --> 49:48.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when I leave Kayenta some
day, it's going
to be better off than when I
came.

49:49.019 --> 49:57.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA STARK: I'm Lisa Stark of
