for the "PBS NewsHour."

49:57.227 --> 50:09.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now, in our
"NewsHour" Shares
moment of the day: that sure
sign of spring,

50:09.840 --> 50:10.807 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tulips.

50:10.841 --> 50:12.709 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And no one knows them better
than the Dutch.

50:12.743 --> 50:19.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This year, the Royal Netherlands
Embassy in
Washington displayed some 10,000
at the ambassador's

50:19.116 --> 50:20.217 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
residence.

50:20.250 --> 50:23.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We took a tour with Caroline
Feitel from the
embassy.

50:23.053 --> 50:26.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CAROLINE FEITEL, Royal
Netherlands Embassy:
Our ambassador decided that,
this year, he

50:26.256 --> 50:31.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would like to do a spring event
where we show
off one of our biggest export
products.

50:31.728 --> 50:36.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we decided to do a tulip
event to celebrate
spring.

50:36.733 --> 50:41.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have over 10,000 tulips here,
and I would
say about 100 different
varieties.

50:41.405 --> 50:47.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Netherlands, we're the
second largest
exporter of agricultural
products in the world.

50:47.411 --> 50:53.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We export about two billion cut
tulips every
year.

50:53.150 --> 50:58.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we export to the United
States over a
billion bulbs, which half are
tulip bulbs.

50:58.655 --> 51:04.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Of course, we're also very much
known for
Keukenhof, which has hundreds of
millions

51:04.227 --> 51:06.296 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of tulips during spring.

51:06.329 --> 51:07.764 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And it's endless.

51:07.798 --> 51:11.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's like a carpet of tulips
that you see,
and it is very impressive.

51:11.701 --> 51:15.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And a lot of Dutch people, but
also a lot
of tourists come to the
Netherlands and want

51:15.105 --> 51:16.606 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to see that.

51:16.640 --> 51:20.644 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it's a unique moment in the
Netherlands
every year in about mid-April.

51:20.677 --> 51:28.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the 16th century, there was a
lot of tulip
bulb speculation, and one bulb
could be the

51:28.318 --> 51:31.188 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
value of a house in Amsterdam.

51:31.221 --> 51:37.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it's seen as the first
bubble speculation,
you know, commercial bubble in
the world.

51:37.661 --> 51:44.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every tulip you see comes from
one bulb that
was created by the grower, and
then had to

51:44.701 --> 51:45.802 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be multiplied.

51:45.836 --> 51:49.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So the one bulb became four, and
the four
becomes 12.

51:49.039 --> 51:53.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so that's why, when you have
a new variety
of tulip, it takes quite a while
before you

51:54.010 --> 51:58.748 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
